# B2B Roadmap Reference

Before implementing any B2B feature, read `docs/b2b-roadmap.md`.

The roadmap defines:

- confirmed product decisions (membership model, roles, address strategy, order aggregation)
- phased implementation plan (Phase 1-4)
- explicit MVP non-goals (do not implement prematurely)
- data ownership and source of truth per entity
- BC connector integration boundaries

## Key Constraints to Enforce

- One customer belongs to exactly one company.
- Do not use Shopify Plus B2B/Company APIs — this store does not have Plus.
- Customer note field is a temporary transport only — clear it after successful webhook processing.
- `b2b` tag on the Shopify customer is the durable signal for theme and app logic.
- App DB is source of truth for company addresses; Shopify customer addresses are a synced mirror.
- Company order history is built by aggregating orders across all approved member customer IDs.
- Only two roles: `ADMIN` and `USER`.

## What Not to Build in MVP

- BC custom extension dependencies.
- Advanced role model beyond `ADMIN`/`USER`.
- User self-removal from company.
- Automated BC-driven membership orchestration.
- Company user invite flow (deferred to post-Phase 1).
